She attended the royal couple's wedding and spoke about them in documentaries about the monarchy. The great-grand-daughter of Tsar Nicholas I, Lady Butter was also a descendent of Russian poet Alexander Pushkin and founded the Pushkin Prize in his name. Like the Queen, she loved horses and owned Formulate which won the Waterford Candelabra Stakes (now The Prestige Stakes), May Hill Stakes and the Fillies' Mile. Her husband David Butter, died in 2010. She is survived by their five children. 